---

✅ STEP 1: Stop registry

If using Podman (Quay or registry container):

podman ps

Then:

podman stop <registry-container>


---

✅ STEP 2: Delete registry storage (IMPORTANT)

👉 Depends on your setup

✔️ If using Quay (common case)

rm -rf /var/lib/containers/storage/*
rm -rf /var/lib/quay/*


---

✔️ If using simple registry (podman registry)

rm -rf /var/lib/registry/*


---

👉 If unsure, check mount:

podman inspect <container> | grep -i mount -A 10


---

✅ STEP 3: Start registry again

podman start <registry-container>


---

✅ STEP 4: Verify registry is empty

curl -k https://mirror1.cl2-mno1-rvt.lan:8443/v2/_catalog

Expected:

{}


---

✅ STEP 5: Re-import mirror tar (CORRECT WAY)

👉 Use oc-mirror v2 (your case)

export GOMAXPROCS=2
export GODEBUG=http2client=0

oc mirror \
--from=mirror_000001.tar \
docker://mirror1.cl2-mno1-rvt.lan:8443


---

🔥 Why these env vars?

Variable	Purpose

GOMAXPROCS=2	reduces CPU/network pressure
GODEBUG=http2client=0	avoids HTTP2 upload bugs


👉 These directly fix your EOF issue


---

✅ STEP 6: Verify mirror success

oc adm release info mirror1.cl2-mno1-rvt.lan:8443/ocp4/openshift4:4.18.23-x86_64


---

🚨 If still fails (rare but important)

Add retry:

oc mirror \
--from=mirror_000001.tar \
docker://mirror1.cl2-mno1-rvt.lan:8443 \
--max-per-registry=2


